<recipe>
    <name>Thai Lentil Soup</name>
    <indexCharacter>T</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>0</servings>
    <instructions>1. Heat the oil in large pot and add the onions, chilli, garlic and lemon grass (or ginger). Cook for 5 minutes or until onions have softened but not browned, stirring occasionally.

2. Add the lentils and spices. Pour in the coconut milk and water, stir. Bring to boil and let simmer for 40-45 minutes, until lentils are soft.

3. Pour in lime juice and add the spring onions and cilantro. Serve.</instructions>
